$ SQL*Plus: SPOOL
@ spool

`spool` sends the output that is normally written to the console also to a file or printer, or (`spool off`) turns this additional output off.

sa:

   → development/databases/Oracle/SQL-Plus/set/termout[`set termout off`] prevents printing output to the console, which
   is especially useful while spooling to a file.

  → development/databases/Oracle/SQL-Plus/sqlpath/spool[`spool.sql` and `spool_off.sql`] are two SQL scripts for
  → development/databases/Oracle/SQL-Plus/sqlpath[`$SQLPATH`] that modify SQL*Plus settings in a way that `spool` creates clean output.

  Using `spool` to → development/databases/Oracle/installed/packages/dbms/metadata/examples/spool[write DDL statements created by `dbms_metadata.get_ddl` to an SQL script file].

  → development/databases/Oracle/SQL-Plus
